General HELP on ^U
 
Use: /msg ^U HELP [topic] to get help on a given topic.
 
@3
^BServices Root Commands^B
*** CHLEVEL      -    Change the minimum level required for a command
*** REHASH       -    Rehash databases and conf files
*** RESTART      -    Restart Services
*** DIE          -    Shutdown Services
*** SAVE         -    Save databases
*** CMDLIST      -    Show command list and status
*** ENABLECMD    -    Enable a command
*** DISABLECMD   -    Disable a command
@2
^BServices Admin Commands^B
*** MASSKILL     -    Kill all users matching a user@host
@1
^BIRC Operator Commands^B
*** SCAN         -    Scan for matching userhosts
*** CLEARMODES   -    Clears all MODES off a given channel
*** OPERMSG      -    Send a notice to all OPERS
*** CLEAROPS     -    Clear all ops off a given channel
*** CLEARBANS    -    Clear all bans off a given channel
*** OPCOM        -    Allows opers to op/deop voice/devoice users
*** MODE         -    Set channel modes
*** WHOIS        -    Extended WHOIS information on given nick
*** XLATE        -    Translates a numeric into its nickname
*** GLINE        -    Add a global BAN
*** REMGLINE     -    Remove a global BAN
*** AUTH         -    Authenticate with services
*** DEAUTH       -    De-Authenticate with services
*** NICKLIST     -    Display a list of nicknames online
*** SERVLIST     -    Display a list of servers online
*** HOSTLIST     -    Display a list of hostnames / clones
*** ADMINLIST    -    List of admins and their status
*** GLINELIST    -    List of global BANS
*** CHANLIST     -    Display a list of all channels
*** UPTIME       -    Display IRCSP uptime
*** WHOISON      -    Display a list of who is on a given channel
*** BANLIST      -    Display ban list on a given channel
*** VERIFY       -    Verify if a user is a ^N Administrator
@0
^BGeneral User Commands^B
*** OPERLIST     -    List of IRC Operators currently online
*** VERSION      -    Display IRCSP version information
*** HELP         -    Shows this screen
 
 
End of HELP
